The devices to monitor people are increasingly requested by parents who wish to keep their children.
The fear for their child brings more people to think about the monitor through a GPS.
The system, introduced at the beginning to search cars can also be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases such as that of the small exmple anicka janatkova.
The instrument is also a big box of matches but will soon be the size of a clock.
The case of the small anicka has moved a large number of people and they have begun to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
"We are trying to say at all that he is not a spy but just another way to reduce the likelihood that there is another tragedy," said Petr pilin of society macro Weil, who is one of the providers of tracking devices on the market.
"I confess that there may be cases of misuse of such appliances, such as, for example, put it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet met with such cases".
"The majority of people are really clients who purchase the product for security reasons, adds pilin.
According to him, the children should always know what is used "the box" and how to use it in an emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana bockova, drew attention if the child does not want to be on to something, he débarassera.
"and even the smallest can show great creativity when it comes to getting rid of something when they do not want to be under control".
"The phones, which can come off as these devices tracing, have already prompted parents to long delays," says bockova.
According to it, the fact that this type of aircraft can assist in case of aggression is very questionable.
"If a kidnapping prepared, he will do everything to ensure that the child has no electronic device that can locate".
"currently, it is the telephone".
"as soon as that will develop the tracking devices, they (criminals) will also seek them because the sale will be supported by a publicity campaign".
"In such cases, criminals will always be ahead of the police," said the psychologist.
She admits that such equipment can help during an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert cech of society RC monitoring, which is tracing services both for cars and people, says that for this type of aircraft can help, even if it was destroyed in the case of aggression.
"The aircraft can be fine-tuned so that it is in regular programme after a period".
"In the case where the device is destroyed, it is just the latest position of the person concerned ”.
"The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer to report immediately to the position of the person who has slipped and is reflected in the elongated position without moving," said cech.
According to him, the so-called smart phones, which are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a similar service after formatting with a special prologiciel.
The problem of tracing systems at present is that it is either a device similar to those that it deals in pendentif the size of a box of matches is the smallest telephones.
We can always lose.
According to pilina of society macro Weil, that is why the tests are being conducted to make devices that resemble common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the possible aggressor may not recognize the tracing system".
"or it will show after a certain time, which would have given the police a little more time," he adds.
That the tracing system to be developed in the form of bracelet or utilisiera pendentif, always the same technology that for cars.
It is a combination of systems for the acquisition of a position via GPS (which is currently used in autonavigation) and a mobile phone service that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
The army has a detonating cords that it could be the turn of the Czech Republic with. But it can take two years.
The army has bought for 445 km of cordeaux used for explosives.
Already last year, the Ministry of Defence had bought 224 km.
The army has therefore reserves to 225 years.
