The Special ammunition size 25 mm to the rifle and containing a highly explosive break, functioned as small grenades.
You can program the ammunition as the contact group of the target, but also to any item of their ballistic trajectory.
It can be used against an enemy who hides behind a barrier, a wall or a gap.
He is not protected from on high and when rain falls over a deadly shards of steel, it can put hors de combat.
According to Richard audette who took part in the development of the new xm-25 rifle is the first infantry weapon technology that uses the "smart".
"The soldier was used mainly in such a way that it found the target, send him a laser beam to determine the distance, gives a precise target that it corrects his included site and based on the rebound.
"say you have referred to 543 metres".
"when you pressez détente, the weapon was fired and the distance of 543 yards more or less 1, 2, 3 meters, said audette.
400 jobs delocalized
The Group Fujitsu relocates its subsidiary of Bad Homburg to Frankfurt.
Next year in July, 400 staff will transfer to Astro park their place of work, which is currently in the office building of the place mareinbader in Bad Homburg.
The Japanese Group Fujitsu relocates its branch of Bad Homburg in Frankfurt.
As affirmed by Wednesday, the giant specializing in the production and maintenance of computers, next year in July, the workplace of 400 men and women, located on the city marienbader Bad Homburg, will be transferred to Astro Park, a vast complex of offices located on the street lyoner Straße niederrad headquarters in Frankfurt.
A Fujitsu spokesman said that in the medium term, the Group should consolidate 100 other jobs still scattered in the region so far.
The supply of rental was extremely attractive. In addition, the offices at Astro Park area open to better suited to the mode of work of staff.
In Bad Homburg, Fujitsu was just tenant.
The General Manager, Bernd Wagner, said: "frankfurt-niederrad constitutes for us a central location with an excellent infrastructure".
He claims that the connection to the airport is of great importance to a comprehensive as Fujitsu.
The relocation of a major company in the region was yesterday the joy of winning and caused the disappointment of losing out.
The Economic Affairs Officer of the city of Frankfurt, Mr. Markus Frank (CDU), said that, once again, a 'global player' had been conquered.
It is an extraordinary act of faith "on location".
Fujitsu is in the city and its location is an important impetus for niederrad.
The mayor of Bad Homburg, Mr. Michael korwisi (the Greens), regrets the decision of Fujitsu.
The Directorate has very soon informed the municipality of this intention.
"It goes without saying that we have offered our assistance to this company," said Mr. korwisi.
However, friendly relations did nothing to change the difficulties of manufacturer of computers with the owner of the building at marienbader.
In the end, the economic reasons have been decisive.
Now it is a unique place if remain empty for long.
"I hope that the owner and licensor of the building will be cooperative."
Ten years ago, the building of the place of the town hall, used so far by the company, Fujitsu and the "small vertical" nearby, as well as the rest of the buildings of the Marienbad, were part of the construction of the controversial spas.
A joint project of the city and a private developer of projects, a new entrance to the town was established between the station and the town hall, which prompted widespread criticism, not only because of the impressive layout of surfaces that were formerly part of the parking lot, but also because of the height of the buildings.
In 2001, the company performance and investment advice, FERI, the manufacturer of computer systems for the distribution of travel, start Amadeus, and Fujitsu, manufacturer of computers at the time still associated with Siemens, moved into their buildings.
In 2006, the German group specialized in Frankfurt immobilien-chancen bought the buildings occupied by Fujitsu in the same time as the Morgan Stanley real estate fund. A year later, these buildings were sold to Spanish society Falcon real estate investments its based in Madrid.
The Fujitsu group headquartered in Tokyo sees itself as the third largest supplier of technology products in the world.
For example, it makes computers and servers to businesses and provides the essential service.
Its branch office established in the region of rhin-main is one of the most important in Germany: Fujitsu are surely more employees in Munich.
The Branch, Fujitsu technology solutions, even Bad Homburg to settle at frankfurt-niederrad. Other subsidiaries operating in this site are Fujitsu services and a company called TDS.
For this, 7,000 square metres have rented in the building Astro Park.
The ancient complex of twenty years, whose name recalls his plan in the form of Star, is home to the headquarters of the Confederation of electronic and electrical engineering.
The expulsion of the server by Amazon - threats against Mr. Assange
WikiLeaks is increasingly difficult.
The Internet service provider, Amazon has removed from its servers the site specialized in the disclosure of confidential documents.
This attitude may be political pressure after the publication of hundreds of thousands of secret diplomatic notes.
The founder of WikiLeaks, Mr. Assange is apparently in England.
In the United States, the website WikiLeaks was attacked with more force.
The Group of cyber-activistes "WikiLeaks' no longer has access to its server housed up here in America and is now seeking a server in Europe.
During this time, the distinguished American senator, Joe Lieberman, has called on other countries and companies to boycott WikiLeaks.
And the WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange, who is wanted by Interpol, is probably in Britain, according to the information published by newspapers.
"WikiLeaks excluded from the Amazon server."
"freedom of expression in countries of freedom", reported Wednesday (local time) the cyber-activistes behind the revelations via the social network Twitter.
Shortly before, the cyber-entreprise, Amazon, had deleted the WikiLeaks documents from its servers.
After the publication of secret diplomatic notes, the cyber-activistes have resorted to Amazon web services (AWS) in order to reach the greatest number of access to documents.
Through Twitter, WikiLeaks continues its revelations: "fantastic, our dollars are being spent on caring for people in Europe."
When freedom of expression is a problem for Amazon, "they should stop selling books".
The television channel CNN, citing the office of Mr Liebermann, reported that Amazon forbade WikiLeaks to use its servers after the investigation conducted by the staff of Senator Joe Lieberman.
The Chairman of the Senate Committee for the protection of the Territory had threatened the site Amazon to orchestrate a boycott against her, told the British newspaper "the guardian".
"I would have hoped that Amazon takes the measure earlier with regard to previous publications by WikiLeaks of classified information," said the senator.
At the same time, Mr. Liebermann called upon other countries to deny the use of servers by the platform.
"WikiLeaks is illegal, monstrous and unscrupulous. In doing so, it puts our national security at risk and jeopardize life throughout the world," according to a statement from the independent senators.
"No company aware of its responsibilities, be it American or foreign, should assist WikiLeaks to disseminate the contents of the stolen documents."
The founder of WikiLeaks, Mr. Assange, who is wanted by the Swedish authorities because he is suspected of rape, is on the list of persons wanted by Interpol.
According to information transmitted by the London newspaper the independent ", the Australian of 39 years lived in Great Britain and Scotland Yard knows exactly where he is.
The cyber-activiste has consistently described manoeuvres orchestrated by detractors prosecution against her by Sweden.
The spokesman for WikiLeaks, kristinn hrafnsson, said in London that threats were made against the site.
"calls have even been launched for the murder of Julian Assange."
That is why particular Assange fears for his safety, said hrafnsson.
That is also why the founder of WikiLeaks continues to hide.
Hrafnsson clearly responded to statements made in North America.
In America, the former Republican Governor of Arkansas, Mike huckabee, has demanded that the leaders of revelations by WikiLeaks is tried and executed for treason.
In Canada, the Adviser to the head of Government of Stephen Harper said on television, clearly so ironic that Mr. Assange should "be killed" and that Mr. Obama could "use a drone".
Meanwhile, an argument broke out between the White House and Mr. Assange.
Robert Gibbs, spokesman for the US president, Barack Obama, has described as "ridiculous and absurd" the fact that Mr. Assange has demanded the resignation of the Secretary of State Hilary Clinton if it was responsible for the order given to diplomats, and leaked recently, to engage in espionage.
"I do not know exactly why we must take the opinion of an individual owner of a web site," said Mr Gibbs.
"our foreign policy, and the interests of the country are much more important than the claims of a website."
The US Government is now fully to test the protection of databases.
According to a statement from the White House, Mr. Russell Travers, Deputy Director of the Counterterrorism Center, has been appointed head to combat leaks.
Mr. Travers is mandated to implement "the necessary structural reforms" made necessary after the leaked diplomatic cables by WikiLeaks.
The White House also has the will to verify the means by which the entire administration exchange and protects the information.
In addition, the US Government announced that it wanted to address the safety of dissidents and activists if ever they were threatened by the WikiLeaks revelations.
"We have done everything possible to get in contact with them," said the State Department spokesman, Philip Crowley.
"We are ready to protect them if necessary."
The University of the lens
“gelato University of Bologna, it prepares the confectioners of ice to best seasons of the year.
The induction course organized three days of future glaciers has been a great success and attracted visitors from around the world.
In fact, where the ice?
The glacier and the ice machine.
The Glacier, i.e. in German the producer somewhat old-fashioned ice cream factory, in accordance with all the rules of the Italian Art of ice.
The turbine to remove ice cream ice chilled the showcase with the help of a spatula, provides in the gaufre and then began to sell.
To his knowledge, there was no need to go to Anzola Dell Emilia in Bologna.
But anyone who wants to know more about the ice, cannot avoid "gelato-university" of the Italian firm carpigiani.
The manufacturer of sorbetières founded the University of ice in 2003 so that the ice cream out of its machines are everywhere to Italian ideals.
The induction course organized three days of future glaciers has been a great success and attracted visitors from around the world.
Are also offered special courses on the lens of chocolate and extending over several days. Similarly, meetings are held in closed glacerie.
In full crisis of quarantine, a number of people dream of a new career, others are simply to achieve their ardent desire on the ice smooth.
This time, there are 40 participants from 19 countries from all continents, Brazil to Saudi Arabia from Hungary.
Jacky, Professor of artistic education come to California is the movement's football-mad slow food. It intends to propose to a future European product quality in the countries of the ice.
Anke Berlin Counsellor in business management and it wants, after a few years, make something unique in this profession rather nerve-wracking.
Two young Egyptian women dream of opening a glacerie in Cairo.
A man from Malta and another time of Brazil would like to improve the quality of the ice cream in their bars, and the wife of Canadian households came because his children love the Italian ice cream.
The master glacier Luciano Ferrari explained to participants the best characteristics of ice perfect.
Is crucial not only to the good taste, but also the flexibility soyeuse and the right consistency.
However, Luciano has not forgotten during training the icing on the cake of the superstructure and, in general, of the South: "The Italian ice is simply the best: and then it still retains a massive dose of romanticism."
The first step in the production seems quite simple.
Luciano provides the basic ingredients, such as milk, cream, milk powder, sugar and stabilizers in a large gas boiler which to 85 degrees through an electronic platform, then cool immediately to four degrees.
Then he opens a valve installed on the machine: it has a white cream pasteurisée basis, the foundation of all kinds of ice in milk.
The instructor was immediately besieged by question: is it possible to manufacture ice using only natural substances without inhibitor?
How can we give free rein to the pleasure of experimentation?
Mr. Luciano cautions were misled by the spirit of the times.
Whoever does that ice, "made from natural ingredients," may nevertheless used stabilizers: the more often a natural product, for example the seed of flour guar obtained from the beans of guar.
It is of course possible to manufacture ice without using inhibitor, just to sell it within 24 hours, otherwise it collapses and the customer croquera nothing other than ice pellets.
Some modifications of the estate are permitted.
This becomes more exciting with flavourings.
The owner Luciano makes the difference between the ingredients that it acquires in the candy or fruit from the supermarket.
In addition, there are the powder and pasta.
"suppliers will try all of you pass dozens of ingredients flavoured."
"However, you should simply try."
Revenue in the fruit sorbets with sugar and fruit costs.
In the ice cream made from the mass of white base, adding eggs becomes a yellow cream and, when you add the cocoa powder, the basis of all the chocolate desserts.
Now, all participants must go to the use of machines to ice.
Luciano invites them to produce four kinds of lenses: vanilla, chocolate, the Moka and kernel with or without eggs in the mass, with more or less aroma of vanilla or other natural ingredients.
The different kinds of ice in the fruit are also subject to the same experience.
Most of fragrances, more fruit purée: from the point of view of taste, it is not absolutely best.
The ice to hazelnuts is not necessarily the taste of the nut, when it is composed largely of hazelnuts.
The ice in Kiwi, very popular, is made from the group using more fruit, less water and less than inhibitor.
"Only a properly balanced mixture is the taste of a lens," says Luciano.
The manufacture of ice is a calculation: If one uses the puree with a lot of sugar, the quantity of sugar to be reduced in the recipe.
A supplement of sugar is necessary for the ice to lemon.
Luciano present a device with which it determines the sugar content of different types of fruit (winegrowers are used to measure the degree of oechsle in the grape must).
Fortunately, the tables facilitate calculations.
The manufacture of the ice does not require, as in the past, as much physical intervention.
It is not only the automatic machine to manufacture the mass of aid.
There is also an instrument which is simultaneously the mixture of ice to make it available onctueux and reduced to negative temperatures.
Despite all the automatisations, small breakdowns are not excluded.
The Brazilian Gustavo is barbouille of fruit puree from head to foot and, thus, éclabousse his fellow students when control of the colossal mixing bowl escapes.
The owner Luciano is of the opinion that an "incident that may occur in every way: it is only a matter of time".
The controllers in an ambiguous position
According to some sources, the industry which is piloting the cultivation of genetically modified crops has hijacked the European Food Safety Authority.
This accusation is now formulated by the Group of Experts testbiotech which is regarded as an independent institute for the evaluation of the impact of biotechnology.
"It sounds like a conspiracy theory, but we are well informed," said Wednesday in Munich Mr. Christoph then, Director of testbiotech.
There are reports that the Chairman of the Group of Experts EFSA for genetically modified plants, Mr. Harry Kuiper, as well as other experts EFSA is under contract with the ILSI pressure group.
It is funded by groups such as Monsanto, Nestlé and Bayer.
Mr. Kuiper has been instrumental in the development of test requirements of EFSA for genetically modified plants and is, therefore, clearly in a situation of conflict of interest, according to the criticisms made by Mr then.
The requirements are developed, by letter, to the position of the pressure group ILSI and bear the marks of industry which, in essence, would be monitored by the authorities installed in Parma in Italy.
This is the second time that testbiotech denounced a conflict of interest.
A high-level official of the EFSA has recently joined without condition or without transitional period, the Swiss food group Syngenta. In doing so, she moved to camp.
There is little time, even the radio Germany Central (mitteldeutsche Rundfunk, MDR) had revealed the existence of a personal relationship between the authority of the European Union on the control and the industrial lobby, which has aroused the suspicions of both the German Federal Environment Agency that MEPs.
However, EFSA admits the existence of any conflict of interest.
An opinion indicates that it exploits all reliable data, including those of industry, as long as they are of good quality.
It does not prohibit experts working for the authority to establish contacts with the industry.
But they should make them public.
Mr. Kuiper admits that he worked for the International Institute for the life sciences (International Life Sciences Institute, ILSI) based in the United States.
The Agency sees itself as a neutral forum comprising experts belonging, inter alia, in the field of science, industry and policy in order to assess the risks of biotechnology without being in the pay of a lobby.
In this case, the independent experts such as Mr. then disapprove of the fact that genetically modified crops are accepted without any testing of food animals and that it was not tested the impact of these plants on the environment.
"We want to know what are, for example, the impact of genetically modified maize in scope," says Mr. then.
The current practice is to test only the proteins isolated and not a genetically modified plant, which makes it difficult to obtain reliable results.
"If we do not search the risks, how can we discover them?" asked Mr. then on an accusatory tone.
This is also the view of Ms. Angelika hilbeck.
This scientific research since 1994 in the field of genetics and currently works at the Polytechnic in Zurich.
In this region, as in the United States, and now also in Europe, the industry is increasingly influence or discredit the scientific criticism.
That is why there are barely even researchers who are not linked to companies.
In the view of the business, critical studies would not be published.
Ms. hilbeck says that "industry control security research".
