Zapatero and the German Red Line
Berlin has opted to remain in the euro, but it establishes the conditions for the entire Union.
Market tensions have led to a Government response doble.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero announced new adjustment methods, which vary from tax cuts for the PMEs, regulation of private agencies for placement or removal of 426 euros in aid to unemployed persons without professional contribution to the privatization of 49 per cent for AENA, the management of Barajas Airport and El Prat and 30 per cent of state lotteries.
For another, the Vice-Chairperson Elena Salgado, with the support of former President Felipe González, unites the criticisms of Chancellor Angela Merkel in relation to its responsibility to remove the current crisis.
How should we interpret these movements?
It should be mentioned that the position of Merkel is not a mistake in its forthcoming policy.
On the contrary, it is a further restriction of the difficult process of redefining the euro.
And there was a dramatic new vision of what should be its future, which shocked with maintaining the old traditions of most of its partners.
The European resistance in Germany are beginning to speculate on the three options out of the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated by itself, Austria and Holland, among other countries, and the South would abandon the monetary area.
The second, the recovery of the mark, even though now it is science fiction, with a current of opinion very favourable, almost a 50 per cent of the population.
The third, a new conception of the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater control macroeconomic, fiscal discipline, fines on countries that transgress, possible suspension of payments to one of them and extension to the private sector of the potential costs of adjustments.
The German position is clear and that so long as it is now, therefore, there was no room for excuses.
Firstly, in 2009, when both the IMF and the European Commission stimulated the deficits, the German Government has invented a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
This was the first signal of divergence between what Germany believed that there should be (plans of fiscal stringency and stability of public finances) and its European partners, France ci-inclut practised.
The second of the Central European countries has been when Merkel has not extended the decision to rescue Greece.
Since then, she has been the subject of fierce criticism, but the truth is that the political consensus in Germany and the public and published were against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, towards the end of October, Merkel reiterates a clear position, calling for the reform of the treaties of the European Union to make possible the rescue of a country and force at the same time the private lenders to bear part of the cost.
This has been interpreted as anti-European, because it has precipitated the crisis in Ireland and the rest.
But his proposal, though somewhat watered down, has been approved, and the following month, we should assist in the process of reform of the Union which makes these measures possible in 2013.
Germany has drawn a red line that it did not believe pass.
And It said that, although now it must take measures with which it may not be too agree, as of that date, the functioning of the euro would have finished.
2013 will mean the creation of a new monetary zone, in which those who break the rules will be severely punished, they may be required to be declared in default, and in that case, the private sector will also benefit costs.
Germany we said that we must follow a strict path of growth with high rates of saving and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and external balances.
An alternative based on debt and the construction, with the huge holes in the balance of payments, which chaired the Spanish growth in the years of the boom, will simply not be tolerated.
The setting is clear.
And it would be wrong not to hear it.
It is not only that the public deficit to 3 per cent in 2013.
What we request is much harder.
And what it does not do in these circumstances is to be deceiving ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence happen to give us greater tranquillity.
And we will seize the opportunity that you have given us, until the spring of 2013.
It seems that President Zapatero has also heard of the form and its twin statement (the reforms promised after the meeting of the past on Saturday with large companies and yesterday's announcement of the new measures) suggests that, despite the criticisms of Merkel, it paved the way for the thesis that it be put to the House.
But the red line that Germany has mapped out is, and they do not seem to move.
And among the possibilities envisaged, it cannot exclude that to abandon a monetary zone with too few countries seriously.
And in this case, Germany we can always say that we had warned.
Sport and fraud Act
The tricks similar to that of Alonso and Ramos against Ajax demonstrate ingenuity but not the will to escape punishment.
The expulsion hatched in principle by two players of Real Madrid (xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) during the match of 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League has caused much ink on the anti-sportif nature of such behaviour and if both players should be sanctioned by UEFA.
As you know, a few minutes before closing the game (as their team already earned clear), the two players have deliberately lost the time when they misbehaved to determine the referee to show them the second yellow card.
Given that Real Madrid will be the leader of his group, the two players will use the regulatory sanction during the match next match against auxerre dam and may proceed without boxes to the next phase.
Finally, the Disciplinary Committee of UEFA has punished with two matches, the coach of the team, José mourinho and different economic are the players involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in circumstances like this or similar is not a new practice, otherwise rather common in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos, rules non-écrites, but followed, this sport.
Part of the debate emerged in the case reported is the fact that this has been a team player as the entity of Real Madrid, who in his anthem poster nobility and honour and past occasions was sentenced to a fine for his players for similar acts) and dramatization, allegedly orchestrated by mourinho, who adds an episode in its history inflated histrionique technician and provocative.
In any case, the debate whether this type of behaviour is not specifically prohibited by the rules contradicted the principles of sport, i.e., whether with these actions it commits a fraud of law; in fact, they are environmentally friendly actions with the sporting regulations, but seemed to sidestep his way.
The issue is to examine the kind of damage they cause to the spirit of sport.
The property, which includes a sporting spirit is the physical integrity of the opposing players, an aspect that, with these actions had not been put at risk, i.e. there is no violent game.
Another of those assets to which it refers is correct with the game that the team of players from perpetrators of an unjust violation of the team, which is not the case either.
However, the paradox of the action of players from Real Madrid is that it does not accept that there normally characterised as cheating o fraud the law, because its violation of the rules had not been conducted in secret to try to avoid the penalty, but their action has tried to be as clear as possible to receive the criminalization of the arbitrator.
They expected and they gladly accepted the punishment.
Another issue is the type of benefit offenders commit misconduct are investigated.
Here it seems necessary to note that it is not in a situation of disadvantage to rival and one receives a benefit in the same match, because obviously the result of the action involves leaving their own team with fewer players.
And this is not a useful strategy for the next match, because the club could not count on these players.
Of course the advantage lies in the fact that the players will start the next phase of the Champions League without cartons that could threaten their future participation in a match.
But this is a long-term benefit, with a degree of ambiguity, because the team could be eliminated and apart from that, with this action, the players are doing a match penalty and spend the second cycle of boxes in which the suspension due to the accumulation of cartons occurs with a less than in the first round.
So, climbing the rungs, this is not so clear that this is an advantage.
Ultimately, these actions are not contrary to the spirit of sport, which is when the same party strategic decisions that promote the maximum advantage that the rules allow.
In our case, the players were not activated to avoid the application of the penalty (this would be a clear case of fraud the law), M otherwise they chose instead the time in which they were submitted to it.
They took a strategic decision without disrupting the penalty or flee.
Even if the border between genius and fraud the law was diffuse, in this context I think it was a clear case of genius.
The controversy, it seems, is due to two factors: because there were two auto-expulsions and how to transmit to the Director for the cause.
The harm caused to the principles of sport by these actions is not as much as ethics, aesthetics.
