China maintains the objectives of reducing greenhouse gases
The representative of that country in the COP16 assured that his country has made tremendous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and a detailed it maintains its offer to reduce until 2020 between 40 and 45 per cent of its emissions of greenhouse gases.
China maintains its offer of between 40 and 45 per cent of its emissions of greenhouse gases by 2020, said Su Wei, a representative of that country to the COP16.
In his first public appearance in the 16th Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP16), Su Wei was assured that his country has made tremendous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and convert its industry.
In fact, a exposé-t-il, the last four years, his country had switched 245 million in efforts to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
However, it was clearly stated that China will not change its objectives, but it will continue to work together with the international community in this area.
It was mentioned that the strategy of China in the area of climate change is divided into four areas: dialogue; building of capacities; building of institutions and support for pilot programmes.
There has been progress in all these areas, ci-inclut approval last year, a new Energy Act, which recognizes the objectives addressed in relation to the reduction of greenhouse gases, a expliqué-t-il.
On the other hand, it was pointed out that in China, federal authorities have worked in a coordinated manner with the local government and for achieving the objectives of energy saving, efficient energy use and emissions reductions.
In addition, a déclaré-t-il, there are various plans underway or completed, both funded by the Chinese Government and the Governments of other countries.
For example, a mentionné-t-il, the Programme for the efficient use of energy, which has been implemented for the last five years and who has received investments of the United Nations (UN), the Government and private initiative.
There is also a draft provincial climate change, another for the change of filament lamps of energy-saving lamps and another for mitigation and adaptation, a détaillé-t-il.
At the same table, Martin M. Krol, Scientific Adviser to the Government of that country in regard to climate change, provided that the efforts of China have been larger than what you think.
For example, a exposé-t-il, per capita emissions of greenhouse gases in China is three tons per person, while in the United States it is 100 tons; China is responsible for 9 per cent of the historic contribution in the contamination.
Similarly, it had made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, how a 20% increase in energy efficiency in the last five years and plans to do another similar to 2020, a déclaré-t-il.
