Romano hunting his first title
Rubén Omar Romano had three defeats in finals he has had ups and downs in his career, but he has been able to achieve three times the decisive series.
With the duel of Santos Laguna and Monterrey, in the end, there are a further two different styles, which are marked by their technicians, who find them a sharp contrast with the results.
Rubén Omar Romano had three defeats in the final, there have been ups and downs in his career, but he has been able to achieve three times the decisive series, although so far it has not hit the nail on the head, and it is for this reason that this opportunity is very special for him.
Argentina has to be content with the sous-champion Medal, he remained a step behind the winners and oddly with the same team he played consecutive final.
The strategist santiste arrived at its first finals as entraineur opening the tournament in 2002, when he took the reins of Morelia with which he lost with an overall score of 4-2 against Toluca; subsequently, in the end 2003 it happened in crucial duel and lost, again with the overall outcome of 3-1 and this was precisely against rayados.
With Santos Laguna already, in the tournament bicentennial 2010, again against the diablos, Rubén has suffered another setback, because his team has done an equal match to 2-2 against the choriceros after 210 minutes of game, but in the range of penalties he obtained an advantage to 3-1 with two opportunities to win the title and eventually three of its players have missed 11 metres and it has suffered the jump at 4-3.
Rubén has lost two finals with the diablos rojos and with Monterrey, his rival in the tournament, so it does not have the same fate, he is trying to move away from maléfice to celebrate for the first time a title, although he says that for him the institution is more important.
"I want to be a champion, I do not want to break no statistics, this is for a club, not for a passion that I have, and therefore I will get the title, but what I have mentioned above is more important," commented on the helmsman when asked what would be its weak points in the final.
He remembers a lot of finals last, which he said that he had learned a lot, "The only lesson we can draw is that until the Umpire siffle the final, we cannot celebrate, we are prepared in line with the players, too, because the last time, with two penalties to draw we were already prepared to run and I think this is a lesson before the end of the game we cannot celebrate".
He knows that the series could be defined by penalties, which is not worried, because it gives his players: "it does not get to the range of penalties, trying to finish in the regular time, but sometimes we have to prepare ourselves, the previous tournament we were prepared, unfortunately the destiny we made a wrong turn, sometimes it is the emotions or anxiety to keep the title in our hands, hands he has escaped, it served as a lesson to the final and we hope that it does not happen again in this position".
Romano now has the opportunity to be a technician sous-champion and taste for the first time the glory afforded by the titles.
The European Union changing the rules for obtaining visas
People should go to the service centres for visa applicants before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost the waiting time would be smaller.
As of 10 January 2011 the processing of visas at the Embassy and consulates in the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to come to the service for visa applicants (ASC, according to its acronyms in English) before their interview in the consular section.
The staff of ASC take biometric information from the applicant, which will be revised by the consular section before the interview.
The new procedure will present some advantages for candidates, including reference to the following:
The total cost to treat the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment for an appointment, another payment for the processing of visas and another for the mail service delivers the document.
The aspiring will conduct a single payment covering the three services.
The current fare will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas with request (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and $390 for the visas of traders and investors.
Those who wish to renew their visas will not appear in an interview with the consular representative, they arise only at the CSA closer to where they will present documents and take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that the biometric information is taken from the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the consular section remain there for less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will pay the extra fee of $26.
For more information on the new procedure for requesting a visa, just visit the page http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / • Boletines / sp101201 _ visas-faqs.html
