14 alleged drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches were carried out in Estrie, Wednesday, in the framework of the dismantling of a network of production and sale of cannabis.
Fourteen people have been arrested and will face various charges.
The searches were conducted in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mostly in places that would have been used for the production of drugs.
"approximately 750 cannabis plants, four kilograms of hashish, money and equipment used for production have been seized," said louis-philippe Ruel, spokesman for the Sûreté du Québec.
In all, eleven men and three women have been arrested, including the two alleged leaders of the network, two men of Sherbrooke.
Those arrested were due to appear at the Palais de Justice de Sherbrooke in the hours after their arrest.
They could face charges of production of cannabis, possession for the purpose of drug trafficking, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
The searches took place following a lengthy investigation, which lasted almost a year.
"It is information received from the public, which has led to the arrests," said Mr. Ruel.
Some 70 officers in the regional cluster Estrie survey for the Sûreté du Québec, the police service of Sherbrooke and regulated memphrémagog, Police took part in the police operation.
