450 million in contracts without bidding
Hydro-Québec was granted to 450 million in contracts to the engineering firms for the eastmain-1-a-sarcelle-rupert hydroelectric project.
At the heart of this avalanche of over 100 contracts, it is a consortium of companies BPR, Dessau, FS and axor who obtained the most important, that of the management of the project, for a sum of $295 million without bidding.
This consortium called energy management was formed in 2004, concurrent with the choice of Hydro-Québec giving the private sector's responsibility to manage this important hydroelectric project in 5 billion.
At the beginning of 2005, the Consortium managing energy décrochait the lucrative contract without there having been to public tender.
For the Party of Quebec, the use of the consortia of enterprises is a serious ethical problem which threatens to eliminate competition and lead to higher prices.
"This is the new way to collusion and shooting competition."
"It is that people, instead of doing it in secret, now do it openly," said yesterday the member péquiste Sylvain Simard in press conference.
Earlier in the morning, Mr. Simard raised the issue at the National Assembly because, he said, to see how the public interest can be used in this way.
The Minister for Natural Resources, Nathalie normandeau, retaliated by afternoon, vigorously denying that there has been collusion to this contract.
"I began to have my trip," she pesté, arguing that the PQ had been "dishonest" and was "deeply flawed".
She said that "it would be the least of things" that the PQ apologizes.
The formula of the consortia is a common practice in the world.
It is usually a time-limited alliance which allows two or more companies to bring their respective expertise to respond to a call for tenders for a complex project.
The project eastmain has a high level of complexity in view of the magnitude of work.
The project is ongoing and will run until 2012.
However, the contract was awarded without competition terms; there have been negotiations.
Also, the formula of the consortia is no longer an exception in Quebec, even for relatively simple projects.
As revealed last week the duty, the formula consortiums in the sector of génie-conseil investigated by the Government.
A quick look at the business register of Québec can count more than 200 consortia, some of which appear to be permanent.
Thus, the firm Dessau works in partnership with most of its main competitors, including CIMA + génivar, snc-lavalin and other rock and tecsult.
Each combination, and there are dozens, back to one and the same entity, Dessau.
The Consortium managing energy normandeau, the Minister stressed that “the territory of James Bay responds to specific dynamic workforce and Hydro-Québec respond in particular since the 1970s".
The big boss of the project eastmain, real LaPorte, the energy company of James Bay (sebj), provided an explanation which has wince on the fact that the contract for project management was granted in OTC.
"If you're going to tender and that there are few bidders, your price will be higher."
"you have two choices: either you take the people who are in even this market and you say: we will negotiate a satisfactory agreement and with a good price. ”
"But the idea is that this is not the price that is important, it is the competence of the people", said Mr. LaPorte.
The contract awarded to the Consortium managing energy is part of a long list of contracts of over $50,000 obtained by the Parti Quebecois.
The contracts were awarded by Hydro-Québec or sebj eastmain-1-a-sarcelle-rupert for the project.
Following verification, the duty were 109 génie-conseil contracts awarded between 2002 and March 2010 to companies or their subsidiaries, including laboratories of soil.
Snc-lavalin won 22 contracts, génivar had 16, 14 and 10 tecsult Dessau, its participation in managing energy.
All of the contracts were negotiated.
