The episodes, snow caused difficulties of movement, including on the secondary network in Britain, and may disrupt certain economic activities.
Twenty-four departments are now in orange alert because of the risk of snow and ice.
The EURE, Eure-et-Loir, Deux-Sèvres and Vienna, were added to the 20 departments already in vigilance Orange, 18 since Wednesday afternoon and two, the Dordogne and the Gironde, later in the night.
According to weather France, supported by snow showers in the north of the Gironde and Charente snow and low on the Ile-de-France.
The layers of snow ranging from 2 to 5 cm, on time of 7 to 10 cm are expected for the departments concerned, and 1 to 3 cm, even up to 5 cm for the Paris region.
The departments concerned are those of the Charente, Charente-Maritime, ribs of Armor, Finistère, Gironde, Dordogne of Poitou and those regions of Normandy, Ile-de-France and Limousin.
The episodes are sufficiently significant snow to cause difficulties of movement and disrupt certain economic activities, warns weather France.
