Hackers and spies in revenge
The case of Wikileaks has a double value.
On the one hand, it is a scandal, a scandal which appears as scandal before the hypocrisy which governs relations between States, the people and the press.
On the other hand, it announced sweeping changes at the international level, and foreshadows a future dominated by the downturn.
But are in order.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is the confirmation of the fact that each case constituted by a secret service (any) is composed exclusively of press clippings.
The American "extraordinary" revelations about the sexual habits of Berlusconi only report what for months could be read in any newspaper (except those whose Berlusconi owns), and the profile of the typical eerily Gaddafi was long for artists to cabaret skits.
The rule that the secret files must be that new compounds already known is essential to the dynamics of the secret services, and not only in this century.
If you go into a bookshop in esoteric publications, you will see that each book repeat (on the Holy Grail, the mystery of the rennes-le-château templiers or rose-croix) exactly what was written in the earlier books.
And not just because the author of hidden texts do not make new research (or knows where to look for news on the non-existent), but because those involved in the occultisme believe that they know already, and reconfirms what they had learned.
This is the mechanism of the success of Dan Brown.
Ditto for the secret files.
The informant is lazy, lazy (or mind limited) the head of the secret services, otherwise it could be, whatever, editor of Libération), who does as true as it recognizes.
The top secret information on Berlusconi that the American Embassy in Rome was sending to the Department of State were the same as those that Newsweek published the week before.
So why the revelations on these dossiers have made so much noise?
On the one hand, they say that any person embraced already know, namely that the embassies, at least since the end of the Second World War, and since that heads of States can telephone or take a plane to meet for dinner, lost their diplomatic service and, with the exception of a few small representation, exercises have become centres of espionage.
Any viewer of films of inquiry knows this, and it is only by hypocrisy that it pretends to ignore.
However, the fact of the publicly reiterate violates the duty of hypocrisy, and serves to put in a bad light American diplomacy.
Secondly, the idea that a hacker can capture the secrets any more secrets of the most powerful country in the world is a significant blow to the prestige of the Department of State.
As the scandal did not as being in crisis victims that the "torturers".
But now to the very nature of what happened.
Once, at the time of Orwell, one could conceive of any power as a big brother who controlled every gesture of his subjects.
The Orwellian prophecy was fully proved since that can monitor each movement through telephone calls, each transaction, the hotel visited, the motorway from and so forth, the citizen becomes the victim of the eye of power.
But when it shows, as it is now, that even the secret cryptes power cannot escape the control of a hacker, the monitoring report ceases to be unidirectional and becomes circular.
The power control every citizen, every citizen, or at least the hacker - elected as the citizen, vindictive, can know all the secrets of power.
How can a power that is not allowed to retain its own secrets can it hold?
It is true, said George Simmel, a true secret ballot is a secret (and secret vacuum can never be unveiled); it is true, too, that know everything about the nature of Berlusconi or Merkel is actually a secret secret vacuum, because in the public domain; but reveal, as WikiLeaks, the secrets of Hillary Clinton were empty secret means removing any power.
Wikileaks has done no wrong to Sarkozy and Merkel, but was too large to Clinton and Obama.
What will be the consequences of this injury inflicted on a very powerful?
It is clear that in the future, States can no longer put them online any information given - it would publish it on a poster I round the corner.
But it is equally clear that with current technology, it is vain hope to maintain confidential reports by telephone.
Nothing could be easier than to discover if and when a Head of State travelled by plane and contacted one of his colleagues.
How can be maintained in future reports and reserved?
I know that, for the moment, my prediction sounds like science fiction and is romantic, but I am obliged to imagine Government officials who move quietly in efforts to control routes, with carriers that messages learned by heart or, at most, by hiding the scarce information written in the heel of a shoe.
The information will be stored in a single copy in locked boxes: basically, the attempted espionage of Watergate was less successful than WikiLeaks.
I had the opportunity to write that the technology is now in crab, i.e. backwards.
A century after the wireless telegraph has revolutionized communications, the Internet has reintroduced a telegram on son (by telephone).
The videos (analogue) had allowed the researchers to explore a cinema film, moving forwards and backwards and removing all the secrets of installation, whereas now the CD (digital) do that skip chapter by chapter, i.e. by macroportions.
With high-speed trains, it goes from Rome to Milan in three hours, while in the air, and it includes displacement, it is three and a half hours.
Therefore, it is not unusual for the policy and the communications technology back to cars on horseback.
One last comment.
In the past, the press was trying to understand what is going on in the secret embassies.
At present, there are embassies seeking confidential information to the press.
Climate: how France bidouille its promises of funding
A year after the Copenhagen agreement, it is time to examine the fulfilment of promises of funding disbursed (so-called fast start and early funding) made by the developed countries.
And the big bidouillages French are revealed.
In the Copenhagen agreement, developed countries pledged to provide 30 billion between 2010 and 2012.
The EU has pledged EUR 7.2 billion over three years and France 1.26 billion euros ($420 million).
At the opening of the COP16, the EU has lifted the great game to persuade its partners of the reality of his commitment to funding fast start: report detailing the action of its Member States, press conference, great side event, distribution of leaflets...
The operation transparency is welcome and appreciated: developing countries and civil society like that all developed countries to do the same with the same level of precision.
The EU announcement have emerged in 2010 to 2.2 billion euros, which puts it on the way to respect its commitment to 7.2 billion in 2012.
But when you look at the detail, things are more complicated.
This money must be, according to the Copenhagen agreement, "new and additional", in order to ensure that an additional effort is achieved without being to the detriment of official development assistance.
Unfortunately, there is no agreement on what it means to "new and additional".
While the European Commission had proposed a harmonization, some Member States, including France, have blocked the procedure.
Today, everyone chooses the reference that best suits them.
The European Commission has, for example, seen as a reference to the year 2009: international funding are maintained, and it adds $150 million over three years to the fast start funding.
Other countries have chosen similar references in terms of the year or in terms of the level of official development assistance.
In contrast, France believes that the funding of all "new projects" of 2010 are "new and additional".
In other words, there is no reference to previous years or the overall level of official development assistance.
Specifically, the total amount of support from France to developing countries can remain stable or even declining), to uphold its commitment in terms of funding "new and additional"...
Another crucial element, the distribution of grants and loans.
Again, there is no rule and everyone chooses its method of calculation.
Some, like France, consider that €1 provided amounts to €1.
Of course, this is hardly justifiable: the effort is not comparable.
If the use of loans can be justified for certain investments that are profitable (often projects related to the mitigation of emissions based on more efficient technologies), it is misleading to present a euro that will be recouped as equivalent to a euro that... at the most, should not be counted under its commitments that the cost of the loan to the lender (equivalent to a rate of interest).
But France did that make such an argument: it "respects" its commitment of EUR 420 million in making 91.5 per cent of loans ($389.8 million euros) and 8.5 per cent of grants (36.1 million euros) - see document from the EU to check for yourself.
It is the only country in the EU to use if massively the loan.
Germany is required to 46 per cent, while Denmark, the Netherlands and Slovakia (other) to fulfil their commitments with 100 percent of donations.
In other words, when the vast majority of the European Union is €1 to meet its commitment, France is only 10 cents and considers that the effort is comparable.
Nice trick!
In summary, in its financing fast start, France operates a double scam: the evolution of the action in time and the reality of the financial effort.
By not spending that 36.1 million euros, she came to believe that she spends $420 million "new and additional" consistent with its promises.
The manipulation of the Ministry of Finance (because it appears that it is Bercy that has achieved the Arbitration) could have a double impact, both within the EU (why the other Member States would continue to give it enough to lend?) and in the negotiations since the developing countries are not completely stupid...
The chapter of early funding is only a small matter, relatively short term, compared to the overall debate on the climate.
But there may be a grain of sand in the vast machine that is the UNFCCC.
Let us hope that this is not the case.
Nevertheless, it is essential to draw lessons from the first year of funding early.
First, France could announce a change in the accounting treatment for the years 2011 and 2012, in a spirit of respect its commitments and equity with the other countries of the European Union.
But above all, France could move the discussion on issues of long-term financing (another crucial chapter currently being discussed): It will not escape the "additionality" or the accounting treatment of loans.
France could change its position to become as progressive on these issues as on others.
The hope is thus based on the new Environment Minister, Mrs Kosciusko-Morizet, who arrives in Cancun next week.
A surprise announcement on the fast start of France and its vision of "additionality" and the use of loans would increase international confidence necessary to move forward in discussions.
Warning to pesticides ingested by children
A 10-year-old child involved in a day 81 different chemicals, according to a study published Wednesday by the Association generations (former movement for rights and respect of future generations).
The Association, which warns that its results "have no significant statistical value in view of the low number of samples analysed, but are illustrative of the problem dealt with", purchased between July and September the commonly consumed foods and one in four meals a day when a child of a dozen years in supermarkets the Oise and Paris.
These meals types, including the official recommendations - five fruit and vegetables, dairy products and three 1.5 litres of water per day, as well as sweets, were reviewed by laboratories in search of chemicals, pesticides, heavy metals and other pollutants.
The balance of the tax base is damning: 81 of which 42 are chemicals that are carcinogenic and five possible or probable carcinogenic substances classified as well as some 37 substances that act as endocrine disruptors (EP), according to studies by various institutions such as the International Agency for Research on Cancer.
"even if, in almost all cases, the legal limits for each chemical taken individually are not exceeded, it is clear from our investigation that the reality of consumer exposure to contaminants possibly carcinogenic and / or PE is worrying," said the association.
For breakfast, butter and tea to milk alone contain more than a dozen possible carcinogenic residues and three proved as carcinogens some as well as nearly a dozen residues that can disrupt the hormonal system.
The apple, imported from Brazil, defined by the study, when this traces of six with a fungicide chemical substances banned in France.
Same thing for the green beans from Kenya, included in the lunch, on which the study detected traces of a powerful insecticide banned in the EU.
In addition, the steak chopped canned tuna, and even the baton of bread and such as selling chewing gum were littered with pesticides and other chemicals.
In tap water analysis revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
For the dinner, the salmon steak was the most "rich" with 34 chemical residues detected and even the plastic base used to warm the meals in the microwave was not free.
The final risk to the consumer of cocktails "spiked" is probably underestimated, "according to the study.
The Alliance Europe ecologie-les Greens (ee-lv), for its part, has proposed "faced with the urgency of the situation" to introduce a moratorium on the use of pesticides, in order to stop the increase in diseases of civilisation ".
In July, a study by the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) indicated the presence of residues of 365 different pesticides found in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
